-- Avusa, Illovo Sugar, Investec, Spar: South African Equity Market Preview
-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-11-18T06:01:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-18/avusa-illovo-sugar-investec-spar-south-african-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may have
unusual price movements in South Africa. Symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  lost 74.51,
or 0.2 percent, to 31,345.17 at the 5 p.m. close in
Johannesburg.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd.  (ANG SJ): South Africa’s largest
miner of the metal resumed work at its Mponeng mine, where the
body of a missing worker was found. AngloGold dropped 2.31 rand,
or 0.7 percent, to 335.19 rand.  Avusa Ltd.  (AVU SJ): The media company announces first-half
earnings. Avusa added 6 cents or 0.3 percent, to 22.16 rand.  Barloworld Ltd.  (BAW SJ): The world’s largest forklift
dealer was raised to “hold” from “sell” at Deutsche Bank by
equity analyst  Roy Mutooni . Barloworld gained 5.06 rand, or 10
percent, to 55.26 rand.  Illovo Sugar Ltd.  (ILV SJ): Africa’s biggest producer of
the sweetener said first-half profit fell to 594 million rand
($85 million) from 647 million rand. The company said full-year
earnings per share may fall as much as 40 percent as trading
conditions deteriorate and because of a drought in the South
Africa’s KwaZulu-Natal province. Illovo rose 20 cents, or 0.8
percent, to 26.20 rand.  Investec Plc  (INL SJ): The private bank and wealth manager
trading in London and Johannesburg reports first-half earnings.
The lender fell 47 cents, or 0.8 percent, to 58.88 rand.  Spar Group Ltd.  (SPP SJ): The food retailer was downgraded
to “hold” from “buy” at Deutsche Bank by equity analyst  Nick Higham . Spar dropped 10 cents, or 0.1 percent, to 98.90 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of South African
companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 0.2 percent to $22.89.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) gained 0.6 percent to $47.31. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) dropped 0.1 percent to $73.80. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) rose 2.1 percent to $4.82. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) added 0.4 percent to $16.67. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY
US) climbed 0.5 percent to $11.75. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) gained 0.8 percent to $30.15. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
rose 1.3 percent to $5.47. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) added 1.7 percent
to $47.61.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Renee Bonorchis  in Johannesburg at 
